        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 26 at 12:39PM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 1239 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Red Gate, or near Linn, moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Linn, Edinburg South Texas International Airport
Edinburg South Texas International Airport, Hargill Elementary, San
Manuel, Red Gate, and Hargill Reservoir.

This includes US Highway 281 between mile markers 748 and 764.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
